<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-06T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Ic/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Charge in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-06T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 6—6:03
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>248. My 247, July 5, 5 p.m. Consulate general at Hankow reports large
                            mass meeting Chinese at Ichang resulting in resolutions for
                            international settlement along lines of Chefoo including international
                            volunteer corps and international municipal council. Resolutions signed
                            by President of Chinese Chamber of Commerce, et cetera. It emphasizes
                            plan will not be detrimental to sovereignty of China.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ruddock</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>